text: Dettmar Cramer (4 April 1925 - 17 September 2015)Bayern Munich lead tributes after coach Dettmar Cramer dies aged 90 was a former German football manager. He coached Bayern Munich. He led them to the 1975 and 1976 European Cups. He was born in Dortmund. Cramer died at the age of 90 at his home in Reit im Winkl, Germany. ==References== Category:1925 births Category:2015 deaths Category:German football managers Category:German footballers Category:German military personnel of World War II Category:People from Dortmund Category:Sportspeople from North Rhine-Westphalia Category:Eintracht Frankfurt managers
